ARGUMENT
x

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_alephfnon | |- aleph Fn On |
| 2 |  | #P_alephon | |- ( aleph ` x ) e. On |
| 3 | 2 | #P_a1i | |- ( x e. On -> ( aleph ` x ) e. On ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_rgen | |- A. x e. On ( aleph ` x ) e. On |
| 5 |  | #P_ffnfv | |- ( aleph : On --> On <-> ( aleph Fn On /\ A. x e. On ( aleph ` x ) e. On ) ) |
| 6 | 1, 4, 5 | #P_mpbir2an | |- aleph : On --> On |
| 7 |  | #P_alephsmo | |- Smo aleph |
| 8 |  | #P_smo11 | |- ( ( aleph : On --> On /\ Smo aleph ) -> aleph : On -1-1-> On ) |
| 9 | 6, 7, 8 | #P_mp2an | |- aleph : On -1-1-> On |
\
 Alternate proof of ~ alephf1 .  (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 15-Mar-2013.)  (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)
